about the unit
who we are
by 2050 the global urban population will nearly double to 64 billion this unprecedented growth in the global urban population creates incredible opportunity but also intensifies the most difficult problem city face such a concentrated poverty crime poor-quality schooling and pollution the university of chicago founded urban labs to help address these challenge urban labs is a set of highly synergistic lab focused on undertaking inquiry and having impact on five essential dimension of urban life crime education health poverty and energy environment urban labs partner with city to identify and rigorously evaluate the policy and program with the greatest potential to improve human life at scale urban labs' evidence-based approach give policymakers and practitioner the knowledge they need to effectively achieve the greatest social good per dollar spent
in sum uchicago urban labs
identifies promising solution to urban challenge
tests the most promising urban policy and program
scales-up the most effective and cost-efficient policy and program
for more information about the uchicago urban labs go to http urbanlabsuchicagoedu
unit job summary
the university of chicago crime lab is seeking a project associate with strong technical skill to support large-scale social policy research project this person will work on a portfolio of project designed to test the effectiveness and cost-effectiveness of promising intervention
this position requires an individual who is able to work a a part of small research team running multiple project concurrently the position offer the opportunity to work directly with leading social policy researcher at the university of chicago and government agency staff a well a an experienced team of data scientist administrative staff and project manager from the chicago office
duties and responsibilities
assists the data and analytics team with data collection management and analysis responsibilities include documenting incoming data preparing file for analysis matching sampling conducting randomization across multiple project
contributes to building traditional statistical model and machine learning algorithm for a variety of research project
prepares result for memo spreadsheet and presentation targeting both policymakers and academic audience
assists with the coordination of research activity communication with partner agency and managing project deliverable
conducts thorough and critical review of relevant literature
